Advanced search

To open the advanced search select Advanced search option from the search toolbar.

To perform more detailed searches use the Advanced search. This Search option allows you to search by any system object, metadata and relationships:

  • Select the system object type (Cultural object, Conservation activity etc.)
  • Specify the metadata or relationships you want to specify in the search
  • To add a new search criteria press Rule

To search for all Projects created within the last month for Paper Conservation Department

  1. Select Project for a Type
  2. Select System Created On property for the Project
    • Select "Is within" operator
    • Select "Last" as a period of time
    • Select as 1 as count
    • Select "Month" as a unit of time
  3. Select "+ Rule" option
  4. Select Department property for the Project
    • Select "In" as operator
    • Select "DCL-PA: Paper Conservation" Department from the drop down menu
  5. Press the Search button
  6. The amount of results is presented in the upper left corner
